                                                                                                   chief information officer                The senior official that provides advice and other assistance to
                                                                                                   [OMB A-130]                              the head of the agency and other senior management personnel
                                                                                                                                            of the agency to ensure that IT is acquired and information
                                                                                                                                            resources are managed for the agency in a manner that achieves
                                                                                                                                            the agencyâ€™s strategic goals and information resources
                                                                                                                                            management goals; and is responsible for ensuring agency
                                                                                                                                            compliance with, and prompt, efficient, and effective
                                                                                                                                            implementation of, the information policies and information
                                                                                                                                            resources management responsibilities, including the reduction
                                                                                                                                            of information collection burdens on the public.

                                                                                                   common configuration                     A SCAP specification that provides unique, common identifiers
                                                                                                   enumeration (CCE)                        for configuration settings found in a wide variety of hardware
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-128




                                                                                                                                            and software products. 28

                                                                                                   common configuration                     A SCAP specification for measuring the severity of software
                                                                                                   scoring system (CCSS)                    security configuration issues.

                                                                                                   common platform                          A SCAP specification that provides a standard naming
                                                                                                   enumeration (CPE)                        convention for operating systems, hardware, and applications
                                                                                                                                            for the purpose of providing consistent, easily parsed names
                                                                                                                                            that can be shared by multiple parties and solutions to refer to
                                                                                                                                            the same specific platform type. 29

                                                                                                   common secure                            A recognized standardized and established benchmark (e.g.,
                                                                                                   configuration                            National Checklist Program, DISA STIGs, CIS Benchmarks,
                                                                                                                                            etc.) that stipulates specific secure configuration settings for a
                                                                                                                                            given IT platform.

                                                                                                   common vulnerabilities                   An SCAP specification that provides unique, common names
                                                                                                   and exposures (CVE)                      for publicly known information system vulnerabilities. 30

                                                                                                   common vulnerability                     An SCAP specification for communicating the characteristics
                                                                                                   scoring system (CVSS)                    of vulnerabilities and measuring their relative severity. 31

                                                                                                   component                                See system component.

                                                                                                   configuration                            The possible conditions, parameters, and specifications with
                                                                                                                                            which an information system or system component can be
                                                                                                                                            described or arranged.

                                                                                                   configuration baseline                   See baseline configuration.



